  "title": "Manufacturing Engineer (Plastic) #79721",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Manufacturer for Semi-Con Industry</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Manufacturing Engineer</strong></li><li>Working Location: Loyang</li><li>Working Hours: 5 days (Mon-Fri: 8am-5.30pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Help develop manufacturing process plans for new and existing products.</li><li>Support manufacturing engineers to review production cycle times and identify improvements.</li><li>Help design cutting tools, fixtures, and gauges for production and inspection.</li><li>Work with the production team to troubleshoot and solve technical issues.</li><li>Learn to perform cost and time analysis for different manufacturing processes.</li><li>Assist with first article (FA) preparation and documentation under supervision.</li><li>Take part in continuous improvement projects, including safety, quality, and cost reduction.</li><li>Training and Development:-</li><li>On-the-job training and mentorship from experienced engineers.</li><li>Exposure to industry-standard CAD/CAM tools (e.g., SolidWorks, SolidCAM).</li><li>Build skills in project management, problem-solving, and technical documentation.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or degree in Manufacturing Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, or a related field.</li><li>Strong interest in manufacturing processes, production planning, and continuous improvement.</li><li>Basic CAD knowledge is an advantage (training will be provided).</li><li>Familiar with Microsoft Office tools (Word, Excel, etc.).</li><li>Willing to learn, adapt, and work both independently and as part of a team.</li><li>Good communication and people skills.</li><li>Strong analytical skills with attention to detail.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#79721 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
